A The Shari’a Court at Rigasa, Kaduna on Thursday dissolved the marriage between Adeniyi Abdulkareem and his wife, Amina Sani over abandonment. The judge, Malam Salisu Abubakar-Tureta dissolved the marriage after Sani filed a suit against her husband seeking for divorce on grounds of 10 years abandonment. The court had also listened to witnesses who confirmed the claims of the complainant. Earlier, the complainant, told the court that she married her husband when he came to Nigeria from the U. S. She added that she followed her husband to the U.S. but came back home when one of her parents got sick. “Ever since he left,I did not hear from him or anyone close to him in 10years.
”I want the court to dissolve the marriage so that I can remarry”, she prayed.